label.value: prothoracic intracoxal trochanter levator muscle motor neuron

value.value: Any intracoxal trochanter levator muscle motor neuron (FBbt:00053068) that has its soma located in some cell body rind of adult prothoracic neuromere (FBbt:00111083).

label.value: mesothoracic intracoxal trochanter levator muscle motor neuron

value.value: Any intracoxal trochanter levator muscle motor neuron (FBbt:00053068) that has its soma located in some cell body rind of adult mesothoracic neuromere (FBbt:00111084).

label.value: metathoracic intracoxal trochanter levator muscle motor neuron

value.value: Any intracoxal trochanter levator muscle motor neuron (FBbt:00053068) that has its soma located in some cell body rind of adult metathoracic neuromere (FBbt:00111085).

label.value: adult prosternal chordotonal organ neuron

value.value: Sensory neuron that has its dendrite in the prosternal (anterior prothoracic) chordotonal organ (Marin et al., 2024). It is proprioceptive (Marin et al., 2024). It follows the prothoracic chordotonal nerve to the prothoracic neuromere, where it joins the dorsal median tract and extends posteriorly (Marin et al., 2024; Gorko et al., 2024). It sends processes towards the midline Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult prosternal sense organ neuron

value.value: Adult sensory neuron that has its dendrite in the prosternal sense organ (Marin et al., 2024). It is proprioceptive (Marin et al., 2024).

label.value: adult ventral thoracic neurosecretory neuron

value.value: Adult neurosecretory neuron with its soma in the ventral part of the ventral nerve cord and an axonal projection to the dorsal ventral nerve cord, where it has neurosecretory sites (Lindquist and Nassel, 1990). Processes also run anteroposteriorly in the medial dorsal ventral nerve cord and it has an ascending projection to the anterior subesophageal zone (Lindquist and Nassel, 1990). There is one of these per thoracic hemineuromere (Lindquist and Nassel, 1990).

definition.value: Lindquist and Nassel (1990) identified an additional large pair of somas (referred to as accessory SPLI neurons/mesothoracic accessory cells) stained in the mesothoracic neuromere, but could not see processes, so unclear whether these are another pair of VTNCs.

label.value: primary head mesoderm

value.value: Head mesoderm derived from the anterior part of the ventral furrow (de Velasco et al., 2006).

label.value: secondary head mesoderm

value.value: Head mesoderm that is not derived from the ventral furrow (de Velasco et al., 2006). It arises later than the primary head mesoderm (de Velasco et al., 2006).

label.value: tectulum subdivision

value.value: Any synaptic neuropil (FBbt:00040005) that is part of some tectulum (FBbt:00007727).

label.value: descending neuron of the posterior brain DNp54

value.value: Descending neuron with its soma in the posterior brain. There is one of these cells on each side and it has a large amount of synaptic output onto DNg02 neurons (Cheong et al., 2024).

definition.value: Not cholinergic, GABAergic, glutamatergic, serotonergic or dopaminergic (Cheong et al., 2024).

label.value: lateral neck chordotonal organ neuron

value.value: Adult chordotonal neuron that innervates a lateral (posterior) scolopidium of the anterior prothoracic (neck) chordotonal organ (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: medial neck chordotonal organ neuron

value.value: Adult chordotonal neuron that innervates a medial (anterior) scolopidium of the anterior prothoracic (neck) chordotonal organ (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: neck muscle motor neuron

value.value: Any motor neuron (FBbt:00005123) that sends synaptic output to some somatic muscle cell of neck (FBbt:00003293).

label.value: neck muscle motor neuron of brain

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron with its soma in the brain (Gorko et al., 2024). Its axon enters the cervical connective, but exits before reaching the ventral nerve cord to reach its muscle target (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult ventral cervical nerve

value.value: Adult nerve that branches from the cervical connective proximal to the brain (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult ventral cervical nerve neck motor neuron

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron that enters the cervical connective, then exits via the ventral cervical nerve to reach its muscle target (Gorko et al., 2024). It has its soma in the ventral gnathal ganglion and ipsilateral arborization in the subesophageal zone (Gorko et al., 2024). There are three of these cells on each side and they innervate the oblique horizontal neck muscles (20) (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult cervical nerve neck motor neuron

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron that enters the cervical connective, then exits via the cervical nerve to reach its muscle target (Gorko et al., 2024). Most of these cells have somas in the brain, but there are also some in the ventral nerve cord (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult dorsal prothoracic nerve neck motor neuron

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron that reaches its muscle target via the dorsal prothoracic nerve (Gorko et al., 2024). It has its soma in the ventral nerve cord (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult transverse horizontal neck muscle 1

value.value: Long dorsal neck muscle that passes above the pleural apodeme (apophysis) and has its posterior attachment slightly dorsoposterior to TH2 (Gorko et al., 2024). It tapers to a tendon that attaches to the posterior head (Gorko et al., 2024). It is innervated by the CvN1 and CvNA1 motor neurons (Gorko et al., 2024).

definition.value: Based on length, position and proximity of anterior end to muscle 20 (OH muscles), TH1 and TH2 probably correspond to muscle 23 in Miller (1950) - FBrf0186027.

label.value: adult transverse horizontal neck muscle 2

value.value: Long dorsal neck muscle that passes below the pleural apodeme (apophysis) and has its posterior attachment slightly ventroanterior to TH1 (Gorko et al., 2024). It tapers to a tendon that attaches to the posterior head (Gorko et al., 2024). It is innervated by the CvNA2 motor neuron (Gorko et al., 2024).

definition.value: Based on length, position and proximity of anterior end to muscle 20 (OH muscles), TH1 and TH2 probably correspond to muscle 23 in Miller (1950) - FBrf0186027.

label.value: adult transverse horizontal neck muscle tendon cell

value.value: Tendon cell at the anterior end of both of the transverse horizontal neck muscles (Gorko et al., 2024). It connects the muscle cells to the posterior head (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult oblique horizontal neck muscle 1

value.value: Short dorsal neck muscle that attaches at the midline to the pronotal apodeme and extends anterolaterally (Gorko et al., 2024). It attaches via small tendon tendrils to the large tendon of the transverse horizontal muscles (Gorko et al., 2024). It is innervated by the VCvN and CvN2 motor neurons (Gorko et al., 2024). It is posterior to the other oblique horizontal muscles (Gorko et al., 2024).

definition.value: Based on dorsomedial attachment and proximity of lateral end to muscle 23 (TH muscles), OH1-3 probably correspond to muscle 20 in Miller (1950) - FBrf0186027.

label.value: adult oblique horizontal neck muscle 2

value.value: Short dorsal neck muscle that attaches at the midline to the pronotal apodeme and extends anterolaterally (Gorko et al., 2024). It attaches via small tendon tendrils to the large tendon of the transverse horizontal muscles (Gorko et al., 2024). It is innervated by the VCvN and CvN2 motor neurons (Gorko et al., 2024). It is found between the other oblique horizontal muscles (Gorko et al., 2024).

definition.value: Based on dorsomedial attachment and proximity of lateral end to muscle 23 (TH muscles), OH1-3 probably correspond to muscle 20 in Miller (1950) - FBrf0186027.

label.value: adult oblique horizontal neck muscle 3

value.value: Short dorsal neck muscle that attaches at the midline to the pronotal apodeme and extends anterolaterally (Gorko et al., 2024). It attaches via small tendon tendrils to the large tendon of the transverse horizontal muscles (Gorko et al., 2024). It is innervated by the VCvN and CvN2 motor neurons (Gorko et al., 2024). It is found anterior to the other oblique horizontal muscles (Gorko et al., 2024).

definition.value: Based on dorsomedial attachment and proximity of lateral end to muscle 23 (TH muscles), OH1-3 probably correspond to muscle 20 in Miller (1950) - FBrf0186027.

label.value: adult ventral lateral neck muscle 1

value.value: Long ventral neck muscle that attaches to a relatively lateral part of the sternal apodeme compared to other ventral muscles and lateral to the VL2 muscle (Gorko et al., 2024). It attaches via a long tendon to the posterior head (Gorko et al., 2024). It is innervated by the CvN5-8 motor neurons (Gorko et al., 2024).

definition.value: Based on lateral attachment to sternal apodeme and tendon connecting to posterior head, VL1 and VL2 probably correspond to muscle 27 in Miller (1950) - FBrf0186027.

label.value: adult ventral lateral neck muscle 2

value.value: Long ventral neck muscle that attaches to a relatively lateral part of the sternal apodeme compared to other ventral muscles and medial to the VL1 muscle (Gorko et al., 2024). It attaches via a long tendon to the posterior head (Gorko et al., 2024). It is innervated by the CvN4 motor neuron (Gorko et al., 2024).

definition.value: Based on lateral attachment to sternal apodeme and tendon connecting to posterior head, VL1 and VL2 probably correspond to muscle 27 in Miller (1950) - FBrf0186027.

label.value: adult occipital condyle

value.value: Stout cuticular protrusion lateral to the occipital foramen (Strausfeld et al., 1987). It has a concave underside, into which fits the front part of the cervical sclerite, separated by a narrow band of non-sclerotized cuticle to provide flexibility (Strausfeld et al., 1987).

label.value: adult cervical sclerite-occipital condyle dorsoventral neck muscle 1

value.value: Dorsoventral muscle that has a narrow attachment to the dorsoposterior cervical sclerite and a broad attachment to the occipital condyle (Strausfeld et al., 1987; Gorko et al., 2024). It is innervated by the DProN1 motor neuron (Gorko et al., 2024).

definition.value: Based on attachment point on posterior head (lateral to occipital foramen) and attachment to cervical sclerite, SC-CO DV1-3 probably correspond to muscle 24 in Miller (1950) - FBrf0186027.

label.value: adult cervical sclerite-occipital condyle dorsoventral neck muscle 2

value.value: Dorsoventral muscle that has a broad attachment to the dorsoposterior cervical sclerite and a narrow attachment to the occipital condyle (Strausfeld et al., 1987; Gorko et al., 2024). It is innervated by the DProN2 motor neuron (Gorko et al., 2024).

definition.value: Based on attachment point on posterior head (lateral to occipital foramen) and attachment to cervical sclerite, SC-CO DV1-3 probably correspond to muscle 24 in Miller (1950) - FBrf0186027.

label.value: adult cervical sclerite-occipital condyle dorsoventral neck muscle 3

value.value: Dorsoventral muscle that has a broad attachment to the dorsoposterior cervical sclerite and tapers to a tendon to attach to the tentorial pit, just lateral to the occipital condyle (Strausfeld et al., 1987; Gorko et al., 2024).

definition.value: Based on attachment point on posterior head (lateral to occipital foramen) and attachment to cervical sclerite, SC-CO DV1-3 probably correspond to muscle 24 in Miller (1950) - FBrf0186027.

label.value: adult neck depressor muscle

value.value: Ventral neck muscle that connects the lower margin of the cervical apodeme to the lateral margin of the prothoracic sternal apodeme (Strausfeld et al., 1987; Gorko et al., 2024). It is oriented dorsoventrally, so that its contraction lowers the cervical sclerite and the ipsilateral side of the head (Strausfeld et al., 1987). It is innervated by the DProN3 motor neuron (Gorko et al., 2024). There are two of these muscles on each side (Strausfeld et al., 1987; Gorko et al., 2024).

definition.value: There does not seem to be a muscle matching this description in Miller (1950) - FBrf0186027.

label.value: adult neck abductor muscle

value.value: Dorsal neck muscle that has a transverse orientation, connecting the medial part of the cervical sclerite laterally to the pronotal cuticle (Strausfeld et al., 1987; Gorko et al., 2024).

definition.value: There does not seem to be a muscle matching this description in Miller (1950) - FBrf0186027.

label.value: adult cervical nerve neck motor neuron 1

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron that innervates transverse horizontal neck muscle 1 via the cervical nerve (Gorko et al., 2024). It has its soma and ipsilateral arborization in the subesophageal zone (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult cervical nerve neck motor neuron 2

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron that innervates an oblique horizontal neck muscle (20) via the cervical nerve (Gorko et al., 2024). It has its soma and ipsilateral arborization in the subesophageal zone (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult cervical nerve neck motor neuron 3

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron that innervates the cervical sclerite rotator neck muscle (26) via the cervical nerve (Gorko et al., 2024). It has its soma and ipsilateral arborization in the subesophageal zone (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult cervical nerve neck motor neuron 4

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron that innervates the ventral lateral neck muscle 2 via the cervical nerve (Gorko et al., 2024). It has its soma and bilateral arborization in the subesophageal zone (Gorko et al., 2024). Arbors are denser in the ipsilateral hemisphere and it descends on the ipsilateral side (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult cervical nerve neck motor neuron 5

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron that innervates the ventral lateral neck muscle 1 via the cervical nerve (Gorko et al., 2024). It has its soma and bilateral arborization in the subesophageal zone (Gorko et al., 2024). Arbors extend further dorsally in the contralateral hemisphere and it descends on the ipsilateral side (Gorko et al., 2024).

label.value: adult cervical nerve neck motor neuron 6

value.value: Adult neck muscle motor neuron that innervates the ventral lateral neck muscle 1 via the cervical nerve (Gorko et al., 2024). It has its soma and bilateral arborization in the subesophageal zone (Gorko et al., 2024). Arbors extend further dorsally in the ipsilateral hemisphere and it descends on the contralateral side (Gorko et al., 2024). It receives input from lobula plate tangential neurons (Gorko et al., 2024).
